        <field name="body">
            <![CDATA[
                <p>
                    <font class="text-black"></font><span style="font-size: 48px;"><font class="text-800">Hardware Shop</font></span>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <span style="font-size: 14px;">
                        <font class="text-800">
                            This setup is for hardware companies selling&nbsp;
                            <font style="font-size: 10pt;" class="text-800">
                                <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Household_hardware">
                                    <span style="text-decoration: none;">
                                        <font class="text-800">
                                            <font style="font-size: 11pt;" class="text-800"><span style="font-style: normal; font-size: 14px;">household hardware</span></font>
                                        </font>
                                    </span>
                                </a>
                                <font style="font-size: 11pt;" class="text-800"><span style="font-style: normal; font-size: 14px;">&nbsp;to consumers</span></font>
                                <font style="font-size: 11pt;" class="text-800"><span style="font-style: normal; font-size: 14px;">.&nbsp;</span></font>
                            </font>
                        </font>
                    </span>
                    <font class="text-800"><span style="font-size: 14px;">Hardware stores are businesses that carry a large selection of products: plumbing, machinery, household, gardening, carpenter and electrical, etc.</span></font>
                </p>
                <p>
                    They use the Point of Sale application, Inventory, Sales, Purchase, Accounting, Contact, Employee, Dashboard, Barcode, and Documents. But if&nbsp;they want to grow their business with a website then a Website and E-commerce applications
                    can be helpful in that industry.<br />
                </p>

                <div class="o_knowledge_behavior_anchor o_knowledge_behavior_type_toc" data-oe-protected="true">
                    <div class="o_knowledge_toc_content">
                        <a href="#" data-oe-nodeid="0" class="oe_unremovable o_no_link_popover d-block o_knowledge_toc_link o_knowledge_toc_link_depth_0">‚ÄãSetup</a>
                        <a href="#" data-oe-nodeid="1" class="oe_unremovable o_no_link_popover d-block o_knowledge_toc_link o_knowledge_toc_link_depth_0">Business Flows</a>
                        <a href="#" data-oe-nodeid="2" class="oe_unremovable o_no_link_popover d-block o_knowledge_toc_link o_knowledge_toc_link_depth_1">Purchase Flow</a>
                        <a href="#" data-oe-nodeid="3" class="oe_unremovable o_no_link_popover d-block o_knowledge_toc_link o_knowledge_toc_link_depth_1">Sales Flow</a>
                        <a href="#" data-oe-nodeid="4" class="oe_unremovable o_no_link_popover d-block o_knowledge_toc_link o_knowledge_toc_link_depth_2">Flow 1: Point of Sale</a>
                        <a href="#" data-oe-nodeid="5" class="oe_unremovable o_no_link_popover d-block o_knowledge_toc_link o_knowledge_toc_link_depth_3">Scenario 1: Regular Sale</a>
                        <a href="#" data-oe-nodeid="6" class="oe_unremovable o_no_link_popover d-block o_knowledge_toc_link o_knowledge_toc_link_depth_3">Scenario 2: Ship Later</a>
                        <a href="#" data-oe-nodeid="7" class="oe_unremovable o_no_link_popover d-block o_knowledge_toc_link o_knowledge_toc_link_depth_3">Scenario 3: Order From the sales application But payment and delivery from the POS </a>
                        <a href="#" data-oe-nodeid="8" class="oe_unremovable o_no_link_popover d-block o_knowledge_toc_link o_knowledge_toc_link_depth_2">Flow 2: Website </a>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <h1>‚ÄãSetup</h1>
                <p>
                    <font class="text-800">
                        <span class="text-black" style="background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">The setup includes:</span></span>
                    </font>
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <span style="font-size: 11pt; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none;"></span>
                        <font class="text-800">
                            <span class="text-black" style="background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">Pricelists: B2C ,&nbsp;B2B</span></span>
                        </font>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <font class="text-800">
                            <span class="text-black" style="background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">Point of Sale with Ship later</span></span>
                        </font>
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <h1>Business Flows</h1>
                <h2>Purchase Flow</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <font style="color: var(--color) !important;"><font class="text-800">Create an RFQ for&nbsp;the required products in bulk quantities</font></font>
                    </li>
                    <li>Choose the&nbsp;appropriate Vendor "Ferrous Hardware"</li>
                    <li>Confirm the RFQ</li>
                    <li><font style="color: var(--color) !important;">Validate the reception for all quantities at once.&nbsp;</font><br /></li>
                </ul>
                <h2>Sales Flow</h2>
                <h3>Flow 1: Point of Sale</h3>
                <h4>Scenario 1: Regular Sale</h4>
                <p>For the Small Products, orders &amp; payments are done at the shop itself, and the delivery is also done at&nbsp;the shop itself</p>
                <p>To do that, start with a POS order:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <strong><font style="color: rgb(255, 156, 0);">Create a&nbsp;POS order</font></strong> with the required product (i.e. TAB Cabinet Handle)
                    </li>
                    <li>Set the customer and then pay the order</li>
                </ul>
                <h4><span class="text-black">Scenario 2: Ship Later</span></h4>
                <p>For large/heavy products, the order &amp; payment is done at the shop, but the delivery is sometimes organized&nbsp;later.</p>
                <p>To do that, start with a POS order:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <strong><font style="color: rgb(255, 156, 0);">Create a&nbsp;POS order</font></strong> with heavy products (i.e. Water Tank)
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Set the customer to define the <strong><font style="color: rgb(255, 156, 0);">shipping address</font></strong>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        As it's B2b, set an invoice and <strong><font style="color: rgb(255, 156, 0);">mark "Ship Later"</font></strong>
                    </li>
                    <li>Then pay the order</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    <font class="text-black">
                        <span class="text-black" style="background-color: transparent; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; font-size: 18px; font-weight: bolder;">
                            <font style="color: var(--color) !important;"><span style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: normal;"></span></font>
                        </span>
                    </font>
                    <span style="color: rgb(55, 65, 81); font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
                        Later, in the Inventory apps, the worker&nbsp;uses the list of orders to&nbsp;deliver in the "Delivery Orders" section. Check what products are ready to be delivered, and validate the delivery order as you send them to clients.
                    </span>
                    <br />
                </p>
                <h4>Scenario 3: Order From the sales application But payment and delivery from the POS<br /></h4>
                <p><font style="color: var(--color) !important;">For Businesses where booking of the order is taken at one branch but the delivery and the payment can be at the nearer branch</font><br /></p>
                <p>
                    <font style="color: var(--color) !important;"><font class="text-800">To do that, Start with the Sales order:</font></font>
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <strong><font style="color: rgb(255, 156, 0);">Create ar Sales&nbsp;order</font></strong> <font class="text-800">with a number of products (Define all the details in&nbsp;the sales order)</font>
                    </li>
                    <li><font class="text-800">Open POS Application --&gt; Choose the related sales order from the POS Screen</font></li>
                    <li>Settle the order</li>
                </ul>
                <h3>Flow 2: Website<br /></h3>
                <p>If the Customer is selling their Products from the website.</p>
                <p>To do that,&nbsp;</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        Visit the B2C Shop and Choose&nbsp;products
                    </li>
                    <li>Finalize the product process for checkout.</li>
                    <li>Set the customer and define the shipping address.</li>
                    <li>Then&nbsp;Pay the Order<font color="#212529" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">.</font></li>
                </ul>
            ]]>
